pragma solidity ^0.4.17;

contract FarmInsurance {
    address public insuranceManager;

    struct Farmer {
        string name;
        string region;
        uint farmSize;
        address farmerAddress;
        address policy;
    }

    struct Policy {
        address insuranceCompanyAddress;
        uint amountOfEther;
        string policyName;
        uint duration;
        string description;
        uint policyId;
    }

    struct Crop {
        string name;
        string season;
        uint predictedYield;
        uint year;
    }
    
    // Insurance policy manager function to define the contract ownership on first deploymenyt
    function farmInsurance() public {
        insuranceManager = msg.sender;
    } 

    Crop[2] public crop;
    Policy[] public policyArray;
    Farmer[] public farmerArray;

    // mapping structs with address as key
    mapping(address => Farmer) private farmers;
    mapping(address => Policy) private policies;

    // Number of farmers participating in the Insuracne contract
    function getFarmersLength() public constant returns (uint) {
        return farmerArray.length;
    }

    // Number of premiums offered by Insurance company
    function getPremiumLength() public constant returns (uint) {
        return policyArray.length;
    }

    // Adding new Insurance policy
    function addPolicy(string _name, uint _amount, uint _duration, string _description) public payable returns (uint){

        require(msg.value > .01 ether);

        policies[msg.sender].insuranceCompanyAddress = msg.sender;
        policies[msg.sender].amountOfEther = _amount;
        policies[msg.sender].policyName = _name;
        policies[msg.sender].duration = _duration;
        policies[msg.sender].description = _description;

        insuranceManager.transfer(msg.value);

        policyArray.length++;
        policyArray[policyArray.length-1].insuranceCompanyAddress = msg.sender;
        policyArray[policyArray.length-1].amountOfEther = _amount;
        policyArray[policyArray.length-1].policyName = _name;
        policyArray[policyArray.length-1].duration = _duration;
        policyArray[policyArray.length-1].description = _description;
        policyArray[policyArray.length-1].policyId = policyArray.length-1;

        return policyArray.length;
    }

    // claim new insurance package
    function requestInsurance(string _name, string _region, uint _farmSize, uint _policyId ) public payable {

        require(msg.value >= policyArray[_policyId].amountOfEther);

        farmers[msg.sender].name = _name;
        farmers[msg.sender].region = _region;
        farmers[msg.sender].farmSize = _farmSize;
        farmers[msg.sender].farmerAddress = msg.sender;
        farmers[msg.sender].policy = policyArray[_policyId].insuranceCompanyAddress;
        farmerArray.length++;
        farmerArray[farmerArray.length-1].name = _name;
        farmerArray[farmerArray.length-1].region = _region;
        farmerArray[farmerArray.length-1].farmSize = _farmSize;
        farmerArray[farmerArray.length-1].farmerAddress = msg.sender;
        farmerArray[farmerArray.length-1].policy = policyArray[_policyId].insuranceCompanyAddress;

        policyArray[_policyId].insuranceCompanyAddress.transfer(this.balance);
    }

    // check if address is insured
    function isInsured() public view returns (bool) {
        return farmers[msg.sender].farmerAddress == msg.sender;
    }

    // returns insured info
    function getInsuranceInfo() public view returns (string, string, uint, uint, string, uint, string) {  // name, plate, amountOfEther, brokername, duration, description

        return(farmers[msg.sender].name,
                farmers[msg.sender].region,
                farmers[msg.sender].farmSize,
                policies[farmers[msg.sender].policy].amountOfEther,
                policies[farmers[msg.sender].policy].policyName,
                policies[farmers[msg.sender].policy].duration,
                policies[farmers[msg.sender].policy].description);
    }

}
